South African comedian Trevor Noah attends Rihanna's 4th Annual Diamond Ball JOHANNESBURG - Trevor Noah will host the 2021 Grammy Awards. This will be the first time The Daily Show host will present the renowned music awards. The announcement was made with the first nominations since the Recording Academy updated its award categories and rules earlier this year. READ: Pop on top as Beyonce, Taylor Swift, Dua Lipa lead Grammy nods Rules on voting were tightened up following allegations of irregularities. Nominations saw Beyoncé, Taylor Swift, and Dua Lipa leading the pack. The 63rd music awards spectacle will take place on 31 January 2021.